data.text:
Zemfira Aliyevna Meftahatdinova (Azerbaijani: Zemfira Əli qızı Meftahətdinova, born 28 May 1963) is a retired Azerbaijani sport shooter who won two Olympic medals in skeet.

Meftahatdinova is a police officer and sports teacher, she speaks three languages. In November 2002 she received a scholarship from the Olympic Solidarity program.

In 2015, she was appointed head of the Athletic Society of the Ministry of Internal Affairs.
